document_data.History:
In the {{YearlinkName|1479}}, Kalen took Vaelis on as his apprentice with the intent of training him to be the heir to the Shadowbane title.{{Cite digital book/Shadowbane|549}} But later Kalen believed he had accidentally killed Vaelis in the underground of [[Waterdeep]].{{Cite digital book/Eye of Justice|5218}}

However, either Vaelis never died or was [[resurrection (spell)|resurrected]] by someone for, the [[1480 DR|following year]], he began crusading in [[Westgate]] as '''Shadowbane'''. Vaelis became a servant of the [[vampire]] [[Kirenkirsalai]] and aided him in a plot that apparently revolved around capturing [[Myrin Darkdance]]. Vaelis believed that the god of vengeance, [[Hoar]], was the true third [[deity]] of the [[Heresy of the Threefold God|Threefold God]] trinity and he incorporated Hoar's belief in vengeance into his crusading.{{Cite digital book/Eye of Justice|5113}}

Vaelis confronted Kalen in Westgate and was defeated, losing an arm in the fight.{{Cite digital book/Eye of Justice|5218}} Near death, Vaelis returned to Kirenkirsalai's lair and was turned into a vampire.{{Cite digital book/Eye of Justice|5354}}
